About 92% dads regret not spending enough time with their baby.*

The birth of a child comes bearing shared responsibilities between the mother and father. And definitely #ItTakes2 to nurture and raise their beloved  baby.
To help fathers get more involved in childcare, Pampers presents an initiative called “Baby Time”. It urges dads to spend more time with their babies with a curation of tips and tricks to enable them to became equal parents.

Download the Pampers App to find out more.

*Based on research conducted by Momspresso MomSights in May 2022 among 405 Dads with baby (0-5 yrs) across India

Supporting farmers. 
Sourcing sustainably. 
Improving livelihoods. 
 
P&G Beauty is joining @solvaygroup and @technoserve India in the Sustainable Guar Initiative to double the production of sustainably farmed guar in India. 
 
Through this program, P&G Beauty will help to improve the livelihoods of smallholder guar bean farmers and their families across 24 farming villages in Rajasthan, India, providing support to more than 5,200 farmers in the adoption of good agricultural practices, including doubling the reach and scale of the program with 1,800 additional women farmers, as well as building a new johad, a community-owned rainwater storage pond, to supply water for household and irrigation purposes. 
 
At P&G sustainable sourcing is not a separate thing we do on the side; it is part of how we do business every day. Click the link in bio to learn more about the sustainable sourcing program in India. 
 
#PGBeauty #ResponsibleBeauty #PositiveForceforBeauty

#DidYouKnow India has only 14% of women working in the fields of Science, Technology, Engineering, Mathematics (STEM) due to unconscious bias that creates barriers for young girls to pursue these studies. It is estimated that 80% of all jobs will be technology based by 2030 and Olay believes it's time to change this equation! The future of our girls depends on what we teach them today. OLAY's #STEMTheGap campaign works towards a great future for our girls - on every purchase of our products, we will fund STEM scholarships for girls across India partnering with Lead school to make more girls pursue a future in STEM.

Let’s STEM THE GAP

Here it is! Presenting, a small lesson on periods that can save 2.3 crore girls from dropping out of school - The Missing Chapter. All over India, many girls stop going to school once they hit puberty, because they are unaware about periods. This important subject is not taught in schools and is also shushed by society. With this chapter on periods, we want to make sure no girl misses out on her education due to lack of period education.

#StandUpForLearningGap - We all love a good meme, but what if these seemingly funny responses highlight a much bigger issue? Over 57% of class 5 students in India can’t read at a grade 2 level. This #LearningGap is affecting over 6 crore children in India, which makes many of them eventually drop out of school.

P&G Shiksha is committed to standing up for this learning gap and ensuring children get the opportunity to thrive academically by improving conceptual understanding. Join the movement and #StandupForLearningGap today, as P&G Shiksha continues to empower young learners through specialized remedial labs, and other learning interventions like early childhood education and community remedial learning, helping one student at a time.

Your support has kept P&G Shiksha going for 19+ years, with over 45 lakh children being impacted. Visit https://pgshiksha.com/ learn more and #StandUpForLearningGap. 

Amazon is a proud partner of P&G Shiksha, visit https://amzn.to/3K8wrsI to know more about the brands that support the initiative.

 
#PGSHIKSHA #StandUpForLearningGap #LearningGapAwareness #Education #Learning #StandUp #RahulDua

On this International Day of Education, we celebrate the impactful partnership with @proctergambleindia flagship CSR initiative @pgshiksha Since 2015, together we’ve reached lakhs of children and mothers across 13 states in the country. In the past year alone, we’ve helped strengthen foundational learning and foster sustainable learning environments for nearly 10 lakh children. Learning opens the door to brighter futures, and every child deserves that opportunity. Through initiatives for early years and elementary grades, with the support of schools, mothers, and youth volunteers, we are preventing and bridging learning gaps and creating lasting impact in communities across India. Here’s to building a future where every child’s eyes beams with hope and their dreams have no limits.

latestPosts.caption:
Here’s a #throwback to the #InternationalVolunteerDay, where our people got together across our offices in the country, to kickstart the celebrations of #20YearsofPGShiksha!! 

The day witnessed two of our strongest pillars come together – our people and the communities we serve, live, and operate in. With more than 270 volunteers across 10 locations, contributing more than 650 hours of community impact, this was one of our largest volunteering drives of its kind!

Here’re happy glimpses of the day!

#PGShiksha #PGIndia #CommunityImpact

P&G brands and P&G people are committed to helping communities around the world through meaningful actions that improve lives every day. Our flagship CSR program - #PGShiksha reflects this commitment.
 
This year, #PGShiksha turns 20, celebrating two decades of driving continued positive impact in communities through a single-minded focus on a national priority - education. From building school infrastructure in the early years, to now broadening the scope and focusing on learning outcomes by improving foundational literacy and numeracy,  P&G Shiksha is impacting over 50 lakh children from underserved communities.
 
What better than the #InternationalVolunteerDay to kickstart the celebrations of #20YearsofPGShiksha, by bringing together two of our strongest pillars – our people and the communities we serve, live, and operate in. With nearly 500 volunteers registering, P&G employees, families, agency partners, distributor partners and NGO volunteers came together at 10 locations across the country in one of our largest volunteering drives of its kind. The volunteers engaged students through specially curated teaching modules, and invested in the learning and all round development of the students.
 
Recently, we brought learning to life—fostering creativity, building confidence, and igniting hope for a brighter future.
 
Here’s a glimpse into the celebrations across sites and locations in India.
 
 
#PGIndia #InternationalVolunteerDay #20yearsofPGShiksha #PGShiksha #CommunityImpact

Thank you, @thecsruniverse , for the 2024 Social Impact Awards. This recognizes #PGShiksha’s impact in the Education category, through its holistic educational interventions which help underserved children with targeted programs designed to improve learning outcomes. 
 
This award celebrates our passion for helping children learn with conceptual understanding and improve their learning outcomes, by leveraging our dedicated learning interventions. For nearly two decades, we’ve been working in communities across the country to break down barriers and bring quality education to underserved children. From building classrooms to improving learning outcomes by leveraging the power of modern technology, our goal is to empower every child’s future.

A huge shoutout to our amazing team, partners, and everyone who has supported us on this journey.

Here’s to more milestones and making a difference together!

#PGIndia #PGShiksha #CSR #Citizenship #SocialImpactConferenceAwards

latestPosts.caption:
Behind every curious mind and confident step of a child is a mother who tirelessly nurtures, teaches, and guides them through their life. This Teachers’ Day, along with @proctergambleindia , we are celebrating Mothers who have been playing the role of their children’s first and most dedicated teachers even before they enter school. From learning new skills themselves to creating fun, innovative ways to teach, they never shy away from the challenge. 

Pratham and #PGShiksha understand this crucial role mothers play in shaping their children’s foundational skills. Therefore, as part of our Early Childhood Education program, we engage mothers to help develop essential motor, cognitive, social emotional, language and creative skills in children, to help set them up for a fast-paced growth as they begin their education journey. In 2023-2024, this initiative has engaged over 4.5 lakh mothers and impacted nearly 7.5 lakh children across the country through thousands of mothers’ groups.

Pratham’s mothers’ groups provide a supportive community where mothers are equipped with essential tools, resources, and training to actively engage in their children’s education. Through regular meet-ups, these groups enable mothers to nurture their children’s learning journey at home.

Here’s our tribute to these mothers, today on #TeachersDay.

#kareinmaaseshuru #teachersday #momteachers #maa #prathameducationfoundation #ngo

In partnership with @pgshiksha @proctergambleindia

Dressed in vibrant colours and filled with #Pride, our people came together to #LeadWithLove at the first-ever Pride Walk at our Mumbai office.

We marched with visible markers of allyship, in a celebration of individuality, unity, and the power of acceptance. It showcased the strength of our diverse workforce and furthered our belief in staying #UniqueandUnited. 

For many years, P&G has championed LGBTQ+ equality, working to create superior experiences for LGBTQ+ consumers and employees that drive growth and positively impact individuals and communities. 

We believe a diverse employee population and inclusive culture improves the ability of our company and brands to win with an increasingly diverse set of consumers around the world. At the same time, we remain committed to providing access and opportunity so LGBTQ+ people can thrive in communities where they work and live.

#PGIndia #Citizenship
